<TITLE> European shares rise 1 pct, oils pare losses </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Nov 22 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - European shares rallied to session highs on Thursday, helped by a turnaround in oil shares, which pared earlier losses, and by a bounce in pharma stocks. By 1444 GMT the FTSEurofirst 300 index of top European shares was up 1.0 percent at 1,457.60 points, just below the day's high at 1,457.68 points. The index is down about 2 percent so far this year and is around its lowest in three months as concern over the impact of the credit crunch on corporate profitability continues to weigh. GlaxoSmithKline, Novartis and Roche were the three top weighted gainers, rising between 5.5 and 6.5 percent after Citigroup upgraded the European health care sector. The energy sector reversed earlier losses and rose as crude oil futures held roughly steady around $97.30 a barrel. Royal Dutch Shell, Total and Repsol gained between 0.3 and 1.1 percent. BP was down 0.4 percent. Around Europe, London's FTSE 100 index was up 1.2 percent, while Frankfurt's DAX gained 0.7 percent and Paris' CAC 40 rose 1 perce
